                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\">&nbsp;</span>",
                    "content": "<div class=\"methodology\">\n<h1 class=\"methodology-subtitle\">About the data</h1>\n<div class=\"methodology-definitions\">\n<h2>Definitions</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"concept\">Proportion of seats held by women in national parliament and local governments</span>: <span class=\"definition\">Total number of seats occupied by women divided by the total number of seats</span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-coverage\">\n<h2>Coverage</h2>\n<p>Women and men who hold elected seats in federal legislative chambers and local deliberative bodies (municipalities) at national and state levels in Mexico.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-availability\">\n<h2>Availability</h2>\n<p>Data on the political participation of women at the local level have been obtained through the national census on local governments,<span class=\"footnote-index\">4</span> which has been conducted biennially by the National Institute of Statistics and Geography (INEGI) since 2011.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n",
